# README for dhcpcd


IMPORTANT

  Ancient Linux kernels (~2.6.x) often lack proper SO_ATTACH_FILTER support,
  the facility raw DHCP clients use to attach a BPF filter to a PF_PACKET
  socket before an IP is configured.

  Modern dhcpcd (9.x/10.x, after the privsep rewrite) treats a failed filter
  attach as fatal, breaking DHCP entirely with "Protocol not available"
  (ENOPROTOOPT) on any interface.
  
  dhcpcd 6.x predates that strict handling and works fine on such kernels, so
  we pin to it here instead of patching modern dhcpcd or rebuilding the kernel.
